  "description": "Taiwan Semiconductor Manufacturing Company (TSMC) is a semiconductor foundry that manufactures logic chips for fabless and IDM customers. Its platform spans advanced nodes (3nm in volume, 2nm in development) and specialty processes for RF/analog, power, and automotive, plus advanced packaging\u2014CoWoS, InFO, and SoIC\u2014to tightly integrate CPUs/GPUs with HBM for AI and HPC. Production is centered in Taiwan with new capacity in the U.S. (Arizona) and Japan (Kumamoto). Customers include Apple (A\u2011/M\u2011series), NVIDIA (data\u2011center GPUs), AMD, Qualcomm, Broadcom, and MediaTek; competitors include Samsung Foundry and Intel Foundry at advanced nodes, with GlobalFoundries, UMC, and SMIC in mature/specialty; key suppliers include ASML (EUV lithography), Applied Materials, Lam Research, Tokyo Electron, KLA (inspection/metrology), and silicon\u2011wafer makers Shin\u2011Etsu and SUMCO.",
